						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in front of the <hi rend="italic">chāvaḍi.</hi></p>						

						<p>Circa 12th century.</p>						

						<p>The epigraph contains the Chālukya <hi rend="italic">pras11asti,</hi> but the name of the king is lost. It introduces a feudatory chief and a subordinate officer and mentions the region of Kariviḍi Thirty. The inscription is badly damaged and the details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
